            . On the 31st of August, about noon, I was near St. Giles' church; I saw the prisoner and another lad - I cannot tell which of them took the handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket, but I saw the prisoner putting it into his apron; he was near enough to have taken it, and was in company with the other lad - I gave an alarm; the prisoner was taken, and the handkerchief found on him.</p>
               <p>RICHARD GRIFFIN EDWARDS. This is my handkerchief - I lost it from my pocket in <placeName id="t18320906-342-crimeloc1938">Broad-street, St. Giles'</placeName>
